{{Unreferenced|date=August 2018}} {{Infobox royalty | name =Charles | image =Charles II de Monaco.jpg | caption = | full name =Charles Grimaldi | succession =[[Lord of Monaco]] | reign =7 October 1581 – 17 May 1589 | predecessor =[[Honoré I, Lord of Monaco|Honoré I]] | successor =[[Hercule, Lord of Monaco|Hercule]] | spouse = | issue = | house =[[House of Grimaldi|Grimaldi]] | father =[[Honoré I, Lord of Monaco]] | mother =[[Isabella Grimaldi]] | birth_date =26 January 1555 | birth_place =[[Monaco]] | death_date ={{death date and age|1589|5|17|1555|1|26|df=yes}} | death_place =[[Monaco]] | date of burial = | place of burial =[[Saint Nicholas Cathedral, Monaco|Saint Nicholas Cathedral]] | religion =[[Roman Catholicism]] }}
'''Charles II''' (26 January 1555 – 17 May 1589) was [[List of rulers of Monaco|Lord]] [[Monaco|of Monaco]] from 7 October 1581 to 17 May 1589.
Charles was the eldest son of [[Honoré I, Lord of Monaco|Honoré I]] (1522–1581) and [[Isabella Grimaldi]] (died 1583). He became [[List of rulers of Monaco|Lord]] [[Monaco|of Monaco]] on the death of his father in 1581.
Protected by [[Spain]], due to the Treaties of 1524, Charles was the first Lord of Monaco who refused to pay homage to the [[House of Savoy|Dukes of Savoy]] for [[Menton]]e and [[Roccabruna]]. In 1583 he was declared, after a trial, to have forfeited those two cities.
Charles ruled for only 8 years before dying at the age of 33. He left no issue and so his youngest brother [[Hercule, Lord of Monaco|Hercule]] became [[List of rulers of Monaco|Lord]] [[Monaco|of Monaco]].
