{{Italic title}} {{Taxobox | name = ''Drosophila virilis'' | regnum = [[Animal]]ia | phylum = [[Arthropod]]a | classis = [[Insect]]a | ordo = [[Fly|Diptera]] | familia = [[Drosophilidae]] | genus = ''[[Drosophila]]'' | subgenus = ''[[Drosophila]]'' | species_group = [[Drosophila virilis species group|''virilis'' group]] | species = '''''D. virilis''''' | binomial = ''Drosophila virilis'' | binomial_authority = Sturtevant, 1916 }}
'''''Drosophila virilis''''' is a [[species]] of [[Drosophilidae|fruit fly]] with a worldwide distribution (probably due to human movements <ref>{{cite journal |doi=10.1186/1471-2148-8-59 |title=Signals of demographic expansion in Drosophila virilis |year=2008 |last1=Mirol |first1=PM |last2=Routtu |first2=J |last3=Hoikkala |first3=A |last4=Butlin |first4=RK |journal=BMC Evol. Biol. |volume=8 |pages=59 |pmid=18298823 |pmc=2276204}}</ref>), and was one of 12 fruit fly genomes sequenced for a large comparative study.<ref>{{cite journal |doi=10.1038/nature06341 |title=Evolution of genes and genomes on the Drosophila phylogeny |year=2007 |last1=Drosophila 12 Genomes Consortium |journal=Nature |volume=450 |pages=203–218 |pmid=17994087 |issue=7167|display-authors=etal}}</ref> [[File:Drosophila_virilis_male.png|thumb|left|''Drosophila virilis'' - Male]]
