{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2017}} {{Use British English|date=November 2017}} {{Infobox street | name = Queen's Road | native_name = | marker_image = | image = 1890s G Washington Wilson - San Roque y parte de La Linea desde Queens Road.jpg | caption = | former_names = | postal_code = | addresses = | length_m = | length_ft = | length_mi = | length_km = | length_ref = | width = | location =[[Gibraltar]] | client = | maint = | coordinates = {{coord|36.132398 |-5.348089|region:GI_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | direction_a = | terminus_a = | direction_b = | terminus_b = | junction = | commissioning_date = | construction_start_date = | completion_date = | inauguration_date = <!-- {{Start date|df=yes|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | demolition_date = | north = | south = | east = | west = }} '''Queen's Road''' is the longest road in the [[British Overseas Territories|British Overseas Territory]] of [[Gibraltar]]. It runs north-south through the [[Upper Rock Nature Reserve]] on the [[Rock of Gibraltar]]. It forks into [[Old Queen's Road]] which runs almost parallel with it for some part. The narrow road is halfway up the Rock and overlooks the [[Bay of Gibraltar]]. [[St. Michael's Cave]] lies off this road on [[Spur Battery Road]].<ref name="Fodor2004">{{cite book|last=Fodor|first=Eugene|title=Fodor's Spain|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=AlgOAQAAMAAJ|accessdate=2 May 2013|year=2004|publisher=D. McKay.|page=452}}</ref> This is a large show cave featuring stalactites and stalagmites and an auditorium large enough to take orchestras.<ref name=frommer>{{cite book|last=Price|first=Danforth|title=Frommer's Seville, Granada and the Best of Andalusia|year=2009|publisher=John Wiley & Sons|page=298|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=qz-TWaAunWoC&pg=PA298&lpg=PA298&dq=saint+michaels+cave+queens&source=bl&ots=lr-vsJx3DJ&sig=FIvrKpLlMRH5jcdUO0tCFVTm_Tk&hl=en&sa=X&ei=osCCUe-5E47xhQepxYHgAg&ved=0CGUQ6AEwBjge#v=onepage&q=saint%20michaels%20cave%20queens&f=false}}</ref> Also of note, apart from the nature reserve, are the [[Great Siege Tunnels]] at the northern end.
